<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Chapter 8 Infectious Disease Surveillance and Early Warning System During Beijing Olympic Games</TITLE><BODY>Abstract To detect the outbreak or epidemic earlier and ensure the public health security during Olympic Games in Beijing, Beijing Olympic Games Infectious Disease Surveillance System (BOG-IDSS) was established based on a series of routine surveillance systems. Early warning algorithms were applied to early detect aberrations. Results showed that BOG-IDSS, especially the newly established Syndromic Surveillance System for Beijing Olympic Games could effectively protect the security of public health during mass gatherings.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>